<hgroup>
	<h1>Welcome to SimpleWorks <div class="fw-version">3.5</div></h1>
	<h3>Welcome to the SimpleWorks documentation. Here you can learn what SimpleWorks includes.</h3>
</hgroup>
<p>We've built SimpleWorks to help you quickly get a site off the ground and to a state where you can easily adapt and modify it into a release. Here's the highlights:</p>

<div class="col-24">
	<div class="col-12 hp-framework-description">
		<a href="/content_layouts">
			<h4>Layouts/Grids</h4>
			<p>Within grid.css you'll find The Grid, a layout framework that works on mobile devices, small screens and full-on modern desktops. It's a twenty-four column, liquid, mobile-scaling grid. It even supports arbitrary nesting.
			</p>
		</a>
		<a href="/type">
			<h4>Typography</h4>
			<p>This page show basic HTML elements and how SimpleWorks renders them. You don't need to change the way you code or learn CLASS or ID names, everything will work by default.</p>
		</a>
		<a href="/form_layouts">
			<h4>Form Layouts/Elements</h4>
			<p>We have tried to simplifying forms by creating two base styles for forms that are tested, include validation styles, have proper spacing. We even included custom radio buttons, checkboxes and select lists so you can style up every form element.</p>
		</a>
		<a href="/buttons">
			<h4>Buttons</h4>
			<p>SimpleWorks includes four base styles, seven sizes that are preconfigured and super easy to modify.</p>
		</a>
		<a href="/ui_elements">
			<h4>UI Elements</h4>
			<p>jQuery and jQuery UI are the hottest javascript frameworks on the market and we have integrated those in the base of our framework. All you need for jQuery UI elements include in the core library, just snap on additional pieces and off you go.</p>
		</a>
		<a href="/reference">
			<h4>Reference</h4>
			<p>At this time this is used to show basic tracking, this article would probably grow into having more things.</p>
		</a>
	</div>
